<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="352" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5727/59.</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">French
                                        Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June 13,
                                        1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                                the receipt of your note of the 8th instant, stating the status of
                                French chambers of commerce, a translation of which I have
                                communicated to the Secretary of the Treasury.</p>
                            <p>It will be my pleasure upon hearing from him to communicate with you
                                further with respect to the subject-matter of your note.</p>
                            <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>